1. To check the lsit of available usb video devices we c use the command 
    The list  will be sorted according to the order they are conncted 

  $ v4l2-ctl --list-devices
  
  You can get information about a particular device by listing its modes 
  $ v4l2-ctl --all -d 0
  
  Using ~$ v4l2-ctl --set-fmt-video=width=1920,height=1080,pixelformat=1 -d 0 will make us able to set dimensions of the frame

